msItem.note:
The recipes provide cures for a range of ailments but specifically focus on gynaecology. In order of appearance,
                                    they are entitled: De sanguine restringendo; iuvamen conceptando et constringentibus uuluam;
                                        Impendimentum concepcionis; Nimius fluxus menstruorum; De duricia matricis et asperitate;
                                        De difficili partu; De ycterycia id est jawnys; Ad laxandum ventrem; De egritudine
                                        splenis; De colica passione; De strophulis. The source(s) of these recipes has not been
                                    identified but some refer to a Gilb[ertus].
